[SN]TITLE[SN]
Y Felinheli pupil referral unit: Trial for cruelty accused

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two workers at a Gwynedd pupil referral unit charged with child cruelty offences will stand trial in October.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Sion Bedwyr Evans, 41, of Llanrug, and Garry Vaughan Roberts, 43, of Caernarfon, face 50 charges between them.
They are alleged to have happened at Canolfan Brynffynnon, Y Felinheli, between September 2006 and March 2014.
At Mold Crown Court on Tuesday, Judge Rhys Rowlands fixed a provisional trial start date for October 17, 2016.
